  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "Currently the Kubelet Volume Manager determines whether a volume is attached by calling the `WaitForAttach()` method of the `volume.Attacher` interface.\n\nThe GCE volume plugin implements the `WaitForAttach()` method by looking at the `/dev/disk/by-id/google-*` file to show up. This is problematic because the existence of the disk file is not sufficient to ensure that the volume is ready to be mounted. This assumption leads to flakes where the volume manager tries to mount the volume before it is ready.\n\nThe AWS volume plugin implements the `WaitForAttach()` method by calling out to the AWS API to verify volume is attached. This is problematic because it requires node machines to have cloud provider credentials.\n\nBoth these issues can be fixed by having the kubelet volume manager wait on a signal from the attach/detach controller indicating the volume is attached before attempting to mount it. We already do this in the reverse direction with the attach/detach controller waiting for nodes to stop \"using\" (unmount) a volume before it proceeds with detach.\n",
